You can create the function `keep_only_names` in Julia as follows:

```julia
function keep_only_names(words::Vector{String})
    return filter(word -> iscapitalized(word), words)
end

# Helper function to check if a word starts with a capital letter
function iscapitalized(word::String)
    return !isempty(word) && isuppercase(word[1])
end
```

This function uses `filter` to iterate over the list of words and retains only those that start with a capital letter, utilizing a helper function `iscapitalized`.
